  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Blood loss was reported as a prognostic risk factor of morbidity and overall survival after
      hepatic resection. The aim of this study prospective randomized was compare the efficacy of
      the administration of tranexamic acid versus placebo to reduce perioperative bleeding after
      major hepatectomy (&gt; 3 hepatic segments).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
